-## 最快安装方式：把项目交给 Agent
+## 确定性部署（已有 OpenClaw）
 
-将下面整段发给运行在 NAS 上、具有 Docker 管理权限的 Agent：
+部署不再依赖 Agent 临场拼装命令。Agent 和人工用户都调用仓库内同一套 Python 部署器：
 
-```text
-请部署这个项目：
-https://github.com/Inupedia/openclaw-nas-media-agent
-
-必须先阅读：
-- README.md
-- docs/AGENT_DEPLOY.md
-- SKILL.md
-- config/routing.json
-- deploy/docker-compose.dependencies.yml
-
-请分两个阶段执行：
-
-阶段 A：只检查，不修改
-1. 识别 NAS 类型、CPU 架构、Docker Compose 版本和 OpenClaw workspace。
-2. 检查 QAS、PanSou、aria2 是否已经存在，避免重复部署。
-3. 请我确认下载目录、正式影视库、临时影视库的真实主机路径。
-4. 输出拟采用的容器网络、端口、卷挂载、环境变量和回滚方案。
-5. 不得输出 Cookie、Token、RPC Secret 或完整内网地址。
-
-阶段 B：我确认后再部署
-1. 将项目安装到 OpenClaw workspace/skills/resource-download-agent。
-2. 缺失的依赖容器参考 deploy/docker-compose.dependencies.yml 部署；已有服务优先复用。
-3. 让 OpenClaw 和 aria2 挂载同一个主机下载目录：
-   - OpenClaw 内路径与 routing.json 的 agent_root 一致；
-   - aria2 内固定映射为 /nas/downloads。
-4. 根据真实路径修改 config/routing.json，不得照搬示例卷名。
-5. 配置 QAS_BASE_URL、QAS_TOKEN、PANSOU_BASE_URL、ARIA2_RPC_URL、ARIA2_RPC_SECRET 和 RESOURCE_AGENT_STATE_DB。
-6. OpenClaw exec 使用 allowlist，只允许本项目 bin/mediactl 的固定绝对路径。
-7. 正式媒体库不得作为下载目标，不得删除、覆盖或清理已有内容。
-8. 运行单元测试、mediactl check-ready 和一次“只预览、不下载”的搜索验收。
-9. 最终报告安装路径、容器状态、挂载对应关系、测试结果、备份和回滚命令。
+```bash
+python3 deploy/cli.py init
+python3 deploy/cli.py discover
+python3 deploy/cli.py plan
+python3 deploy/cli.py apply --plan-id PLAN_ID --confirmed
+python3 deploy/cli.py verify --level safe
 ```
 
-更完整的机器执行规则见 **[Agent 部署手册](docs/AGENT_DEPLOY.md)**。
+部署器使用 `deploy/config.yaml` 作为唯一配置源，使用独立 `deploy/secrets/` 保存密码、Cookie、Token 和代理配置。它负责只读发现、不可变计划、固定镜像、配置渲染、事务日志、分层验收和回滚。
+
+只有登录、扫码、验证码、冲突选择和危险操作确认需要用户参与。首版正式支持绿联 UGOS 和标准 Linux Docker，其他 NAS 平台按实验性兼容处理。
+
+详细步骤见 **[快速部署](docs/deployment/QUICKSTART.md)** 和 **[已有 OpenClaw 模式](docs/deployment/EXISTING_OPENCLAW.md)**。
 
 ## 手动部署
 
diff --git a/deploy/docker-compose.dependencies.yml b/deploy/docker-compose.dependencies.yml
index 4a230d2..b828fe3 100644
--- a/deploy/docker-compose.dependencies.yml
+++ b/deploy/docker-compose.dependencies.yml
@@ -1,98 +1,70 @@
-# Reference dependency stack for openclaw-nas-media-agent.
-#
-# This file is intentionally separate from OpenClaw. Reuse existing QAS,
-# PanSou, or aria2 containers whenever possible. Review every host path,
-# port, credential, image tag, and UID/GID before starting it on a NAS.
-#
-# QAS still needs its own Quark account configuration, API token, and aria2
-# plugin/RPC settings in the QAS WebUI. This Compose file does not configure
-# account cookies or grant permission to download third-party copyrighted work.
-
 name: openclaw-media-dependencies
 
 services:
   qas:
-    image: cp0204/quark-auto-save:latest
+    image: "cp0204/quark-auto-save@sha256:4d97439c0cd095c5fb8ef7133ca4726c8a3f996fa319f8c049180270b61c29be"
     container_name: openclaw-media-qas
     restart: unless-stopped
     environment:
-      TZ: ${TZ:-Asia/Shanghai}
-      WEBUI_USERNAME: ${QAS_WEBUI_USERNAME:?set QAS_WEBUI_USERNAME in .env}
-      WEBUI_PASSWORD: ${QAS_WEBUI_PASSWORD:?set QAS_WEBUI_PASSWORD in .env}
+      TZ: "Asia/Shanghai"
+      WEBUI_USERNAME: "admin"
+      WEBUI_PASSWORD: "${QAS_WEBUI_PASSWORD:?loaded by deployer}"
     volumes:
-      - ${QAS_CONFIG_DIR:?set QAS_CONFIG_DIR in .env}:/app/config
+      - type: bind
+        source: "/volume1/docker/openclaw-media/qas/config"
+        target: /app/config
     ports:
-      # Localhost binding is safer. OpenClaw should access qas:5005
-      # through the shared Docker network.
-      - 127.0.0.1:${QAS_PORT:-5005}:5005
+      - "127.0.0.1:${QAS_PORT:-5005}:5005"
     networks:
       - media
 
   pansou:
-    image: ghcr.io/fish2018/pansou:latest
+    image: "ghcr.io/fish2018/pansou@sha256:9627039c1f081e9a5668f7897ff52c32a79cd7e8422349d659f4192e317bf693"
     container_name: openclaw-media-pansou
     restart: unless-stopped
     environment:
-      TZ: ${TZ:-Asia/Shanghai}
+      TZ: "Asia/Shanghai"
       PORT: "8888"
-      CHANNELS: ${PANSOU_CHANNELS:-tgsearchers3}
-      ENABLED_PLUGINS: ${PANSOU_ENABLED_PLUGINS:-}
+      CHANNELS: "tgsearchers3"
+      ENABLED_PLUGINS: ""
       CACHE_PATH: /app/cache
+      PROXY: "${PANSOU_PROXY_URL:-}"
+      HTTP_PROXY: "${PANSOU_HTTP_PROXY:-}"
+      HTTPS_PROXY: "${PANSOU_HTTPS_PROXY:-}"
     volumes:
-      - ${PANSOU_CACHE_DIR:?set PANSOU_CACHE_DIR in .env}:/app/cache
+      - type: bind
+        source: "/volume1/docker/openclaw-media/pansou/cache"
+        target: /app/cache
     ports:
-      - 127.0.0.1:${PANSOU_PORT:-8888}:8888
+      - "127.0.0.1:${PANSOU_PORT:-8888}:8888"
     networks:
       - media
 
   aria2:
-    image: p3terx/aria2-pro:latest
+    image: "p3terx/aria2-pro@sha256:086d1a37c586edb07ec0fb956bf9edd89d1d38d138ad5309ff96d510c8c9a011"
     container_name: openclaw-media-aria2
     restart: unless-stopped
     environment:
-      TZ: ${TZ:-Asia/Shanghai}
-      PUID: ${PUID:-1000}
-      PGID: ${PGID:-1000}
-      RPC_SECRET: ${ARIA2_RPC_SECRET:?set ARIA2_RPC_SECRET in .env}
+      TZ: "Asia/Shanghai"
+      PUID: "${PUID:-1000}"
+      PGID: "${PGID:-1000}"
+      RPC_SECRET: "${ARIA2_RPC_SECRET:?loaded by deployer}"
       RPC_PORT: "6800"
       LISTEN_PORT: "6888"
     volumes:
-      - ${ARIA2_CONFIG_DIR:?set ARIA2_CONFIG_DIR in .env}:/config
-      # The Skill submits task paths under /nas/downloads/.incoming/...
-      - ${DOWNLOADS_DIR:?set DOWNLOADS_DIR in .env}:/nas/downloads
+      - type: bind
+        source: "/volume1/docker/openclaw-media/aria2/config"
+        target: /config
+      - type: bind
+        source: "/volume2/downloads"
+        target: /nas/downloads
     ports:
-      # Keep RPC bound to localhost unless a different host must access it.
-      # OpenClaw on the shared network should use aria2:6800.
-      - 127.0.0.1:${ARIA2_RPC_PORT:-6800}:6800
-      - 6888:6888
-      - 6888:6888/udp
+      - "127.0.0.1:${ARIA2_RPC_PORT:-6800}:6800"
+      - "6888:6888"
+      - "6888:6888/udp"
     networks:
